# {{ site.businessName }} — Sub-Metering for Landlords

> {{ site.businessName }} installs clip-on electricity sub-meters in multi-unit rental properties across {{ site.serviceArea }}. If your building has one meter and multiple units, you're covering everyone's electricity. I fix that.

## What I Do

I install clip-on sub-meters (current transformers) that give each unit in a multi-unit property its own electricity measurement. The meters clamp around existing wiring without touching it — no rewiring, no cutting, no damage, no permits required. Installation takes under 1 hour. Tenants pay for what they use. Landlords stop subsidizing hydro.

## What This Is NOT

This is not electrical work. I don't cut wires, modify panels, or rewire anything. The device is a clip-on current transformer — it clamps around the cable like a clothespin. No ESA certification required. No permits needed. No power shutoff during installation. 100% reversible — remove the clip and the panel goes back to exactly how it was.

## Service Area

**Hamilton, Ontario** and **Burlington, Ontario**.

## How It Works

1. **I come look at your panel** — Takes 15 minutes. I check if your building's wiring lets me isolate each unit's circuit. Most buildings do. If yours doesn't, I'll tell you on the spot and you don't owe me anything.
2. **I clip the meters on** — The meter is a small clamp that goes around the wire. I don't cut anything. I don't touch the conductor. Takes about an hour for a typical fourplex.
3. **You open the dashboard** — Same day. Each unit shows up on your phone. Hourly, daily, monthly usage.

## Key Facts

- **Legal basis**: Ontario Regulation 394/10 under the Electricity Act
- **Device type**: Clip-on current transformers (non-invasive)
- **Electrician required**: No — this is a monitoring device, not electrical modification
- **Permits required**: No
- **Power shutoff**: No
- **Reversible**: Yes — remove the clip and the panel is unchanged
- **Pricing**: {{ site.pricing.perUnit }} per unit (one-time), no monthly fees
- **ROI**: Most landlords make it back in {{ site.pricing.roiMonths }} months
- **Properties served**: Duplexes, triplexes, fourplexes, townhouse blocks, small apartments (2+ units sharing one meter)

